that their fold curves turn around in the\nintermediate-frequency regime. We identify the mechanism responsible for this\nturning. Finally, we show that the fvdP equation is a normal form for a class\nof single-frequency periodically-driven slow/fast systems with two fast\nvariables and one slow variable which possess a nondegenerate fold of limit\ncycles.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 15 Apr 2015 16:59:03 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-01-20"}
